(b) The separate commemoration of the Apostles. Till the eighth century, they were jointly commemorated on June 19, in the West, and on June 30, in the East of Christendom². Hence there isa good deal of uncertainty and variety in the wording, etc. of these Missae. A trace' of this older arrangement might seem to be found in the title written for July 6, ‘In octauis Apostolorum' (p. 149), but the Collect refers only to St.1>eter and St. Paul.
